-56a7a67c"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-430ccfec">How to use essential oils in the sauna<br></span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-25af5de8"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-cfec1d65">Before using the oil, it must be diluted in water. The most common method is to add a few drops of essential oil to the water bucket in the sauna. When you then pour the water over the hot stones, the steam will give a pleasant scent. Diluting the oil in water reduces intense exposure since essential oils have strong aromas, and it is also safer, reducing the risk of flammability.
